          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make and blind bake the pastry case",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Rub the butter into the flour and icing sugar until the mixture resembles fine breadcrumbs. Add the egg yolk and water and bring together. Wrap and refrigerate for 30 minutes. Preheat the oven to 190°C conventional. Roll the pastry to 3 mm and line a 23 cm loose-bottomed tart tin. Line with baking paper and fill with baking beans. Bake for 20 minutes, remove the beans and paper, and bake for a further 8 to 10 minutes until the base is dry and pale gold. Cool completely.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the coconut pastry cream",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Whisk the egg yolks, sugar, and cornflour together. Bring the coconut milk and whole milk to a simmer. Pour a third over the egg mixture while whisking to temper, then return to the pan and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until very thick. Stir in the desiccated coconut. Press cling film directly onto the surface and refrigerate until cold.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Assemble",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Toast the 30 g desiccated coconut in a dry pan until golden. Set aside to cool. Beat the cold coconut pastry cream briefly to loosen it and spoon into the baked pastry case, smoothing the top. Spoon or pipe the lightly whipped cream over the filling. Scatter the toasted coconut over the top. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
